'''Lota Schwager''' is a [[Chilean people|Chilean]] professional team based in [[Coronel, Chile|Coronel]] that currently play in [[Segunda División de Chile|Segunda División Profesional]] (third-tier).

==History==
Following the merger between [[:es:Federico Schwager|Federico Schwager]] and Minas Lota (teams that competed in [[:es:Campeonato Regional de Concepción|Campeonato Regional de Concepción]] representing [[Lota, Chile|Lota]] and Schwager companies), the club was established on 10 May 1966 under the name of ''"Lota Schwager"'', making reference to both companies latest mentioned. Having their debut–season the same year (where they finished ninth, after a poor campaign), "The Little Lamp" under the coach [[:es:Isaac Carrasco|Isaac Carrasco]] achieved its first promotion to top-division in 1969, where Coronel-based team remained until 1980.

After they won their second [[Primera B (Chile)|Primera B]] title in 1986, Lota returned to first-tier thanks to manager [[:es:Juan Carlos Gangas|Juan Carlos Gangas]]' job, but they only stayed at [[Chilean Primera División|Primera División]] one season, after of defeat the Promotion Play-offs against [[O'Higgins F.C.|O'Higgins]] and [[Regional Atacama]]. Following Coronel mining-crisis of 1994, the club disappeared during seven years, starting out again in 2001 for play as an amateur team in [[Tercera División de Chile|Tercera División]], winning that in they first attempt to reach it.

In 2006, after a good campaign in secondgontier (where even so were four managers who coached Lota: [[:es:Leonardo Vinés|Leonardo Vinés]], Humberto López, Márcio da Silva and Jaime Nova), finishing third in the table behind the champion [[Deportes Melipilla]] and runner-up [[Ñublense]], the team played the Promotion Play-offs against [[Talca]]-based club [[C.S.D. Rangers|Rangers]], which won at their home stadium [[Estadio Federico Schwager|Federico Schwager]] on the penalties thanks to [[Cristián Limenza]]'s performances in the goal saving penalties.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablesc/chile06.html |title=Chile 2006 |publisher=Rsssf.com |date=2007-02-21 |accessdate=2013-10-12}}</ref>

