{{Use Pakistani English|date=April 2016}} {{Infobox cricket team |name= United Bank Limited |image= [[File:United_Bank,_Pakistan,_logo.png]] |colours= {{color box|Blue}} |Head=[[Nadeem khan]] |coach= [[Umer Rashid]] |captain=[[Shan Masood]] |founded= 1975 |title1 = |title1wins = |ground= [[United Bank Limited Sports Complex]] |capacity= |owner= [[United Bank Limited Pakistan]] |website= [http://www.ubldirect.com www.ubldirect.com] }} '''United Bank Limited cricket team''' was a [[first-class cricket]] team in [[Pakistan]], sponsored by [[United Bank Limited Pakistan]], which was founded in 1975.<ref name="CI">{{cite web|url=http://www.espncricinfo.com/story/_/id/23649637/united-bank-limited-ubl-mulls-pulling-pakistan-domestic-circuit |title=UBL mulls pulling out of Pakistan's domestic circuit |work=ESPN Cricinfo |accessdate=30 May 2018}}</ref> They have competed in various domestic competitions since 1975-76, winning ten championship trophies to date. They initially left domestic cricket in Pakistan in 1997, before returning in 2011.<ref name="dis">{{cite web|url=http://www.espncricinfo.com/story/_/id/24069285/younis-khan-quits-ubl-franchise-pulls-domestic-circuit |title=Younis Khan quits UBL after franchise pulls out of domestic circuit |work=ESPN Cricinfo |accessdate=11 July 2018}}</ref> They played their home games at the [[United Bank Limited Sports Complex]] in [[Karachi]].<ref name="Cricinfo">{{Cite web|url=http://www.espncricinfo.com/pakistan/content/ground/58959.html |title=United Bank Limited Sports Complex |accessdate=17 September 2016 |work=ESPN Cricinfo}}</ref>
In July 2018, United Bank Limited disbanded the team, with captain [[Younis Khan]] resigning as a result.<ref name="dis"/>
