'''YMPC Cricket Club''' is a [[cricket]] club in [[Barbados]]. The club plays in the [[Barbados Cricket Association]] Division 1 championship. The club is part of the Young Men's Progressive Club of Barbados; established in 1935 for "lower middle income whites and near whites for whom there was no space in [[Pickwick Cricket Club|Pickwick]] and [[Wanderers Cricket Club|Wanderers]] [cricket clubs]".<ref>Sandiford, p. 20.</ref> Changes in Barbadian society meant that from the 1960s onwards, the membership of YMPC gradually came to reflect the general Barbadian population.<ref>Sandiford, p. 22.</ref> YMPC's home ground is at Beckles Road, [[Saint Michael, Barbados|Saint Michael]].<ref name=HomeGround>{{cite news|title=Narrow win for YMPC|url=http://www.nationnews.com/index.php/articles/view/narrow-win-for-ympc/|accessdate=5 July 2011|newspaper=The Nation|date=25 January 2011|quote=The most exciting finish of the day came at Beckles Road where host YMPC ...}}</ref> The club motto is ''[[mens sana in corpore sano]].''
YMPC won the 2006 Division 1 championship&mdash;the club's third&mdash;only eight years after a mass exodus of leading players threatened the future of the club.<ref name=High>{{cite news|last=Gill|first=Haydn|title=YMPC high!|url=http://barpublish.bits.baseview.com/story/299874928622082.php|accessdate=4 July 2011|newspaper=The Nation|date=27 September 2006}}</ref> The club's previous championship was shared with [[Empire Cricket Club]] in 1991.<ref name=empire1991>{{cite news|last=Gill|first=Haydn|title=Let's hear it for YMPC!|url=http://barpublish.bits.baseview.com/story/292572963293710.php|accessdate=4 July 2011|newspaper=The Nation|date=25 September 2006}}</ref>
Notable players include [[West Indies cricket team|West Indies]] [[Test cricket]]ers: *[[Joel Garner]]<ref name=Pollard>{{cite web|last=Holder|first=Keith|title=BCUA umpire and former BCA Division 1 batsman Anthony Pollard to be buried on Friday|url=http://www.bcacricket.org/2010/articles.php?link=1810|publisher=Barbados Cricket Association|accessdate=4 July 2011|date=13 May 2010}}</ref> *[[Collis King]]<ref name=Pollard /> *[[Fidel Edwards]]<ref name=High /> *[[Dwayne Smith]]<ref name=High />
